## Backfill note (added 2026-04-26 retroactively)

## Conversation
User reported player-chip text was illegible in dark mode (cream-on-cream
on light random hues). Filed as #52.

## Actions
- Found `colorForPlayer(id)` in `lib/player.ts` returning HSL(h, 80%, 65%).
- Added `chipColorsForPlayer(id)` returning `{ bg, ink }` where ink is
  picked by WCAG relative luminance from the chip's HSL — dark ink on
  light bg, cream ink on dark bg.
- Added `--chip-ink` CSS variable that `.player-chip` honors with
  `--game-ink` as the default for back-compat.
- Updated 17 chip call sites across game-client, lobby-client, recap,
  daily, leaders, profile-stats, chat-panel, etc.
- Pinned `/leaders` medal chips (gold/cream/bronze) to dark ink since
  they're always light regardless of theme.

